rComments: Même si je déteste la comptabilité, jai apprécié que le professeur prenne les commentaires des étudiants de façon constructive par exemple en diminuant le temps nécessaire pour compléter Le Devoir 2. Les polls interactifs étaient stimulants et je crois quil devrait y en avoir encore plus. Le manuel du cours ma semblé un peu inutile par contre,
Un cours difficile, mais c'était attendu du fait que c'est un cours synthèse. Le prof connait bien la matière et connait bien comment faire des études de cas.

Rough class. Grading expectations are WAY to high and the work load is crazy. The professor will laugh in your face when correcting the cases in class and will NOT help you if you have problems. The worst part is, he didn't teach us anything and he expected us to know everything. Would absolutely not recommend this class.

This prof is one of the best profs Ive ever had! Since he is so young he has a much better teaching style than all the old antiquated tenured profs at uOttawa. He is inspirational since hes already achieved so much at such a young age. His midterm was very fair, and if you studied hard, then you would succeed. Final was a bit too long. A gem!
Bon prof, la matière est en général bien enseigner, j'ai trouvé que le prof s'améliorait au fil de la session et il c'est très bien adapté aux classes à distance.

He doesn't really have a unique teaching style, and focuses most of his efforts on directing you to the CPA handbook instead of focusing on in-class problem solving. That being said the midterm was very fair, and the assignments reflect course content. However, beware of the final which is nearly impossible to finish, and based on obscure concepts.
Really tough course, but that's Inter. Sometimes he gives funny audit stories to reign us back in. Jia really knows his content because he used to TA.
